Body. Ratio lengths of Abd IV/III=4 (n=20). Trochanteral organ from 14–30 spiny chaetae. Unguis with 4 teeth on internal edge, first pair at 55% from base of unguis, and of 2 unpaired teeth, first one at 71% from base and most distal one minute. Dorsal tooth intermediate between internal pair and base of the unguis. Unguiculus spike–like, with smooth external edge on leg III. Manubrial plate with 3 chaetae and 2 psp. Mucro with 2 teeth, subapical tooth smaller than the apical one. Mucronal spine present (
